com.foreach.across.modules.spring.security.acl.business

Class AclPermission

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.springframework.security.acls.domain.AbstractPermission
      • com.foreach.across.modules.spring.security.acl.business.AclPermission
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, org.springframework.security.acls.model.Permission

    public class AclPermission
extends org.springframework.security.acls.domain.AbstractPermission
    Redefined instance of BasePermission to avoid confusion with the Permission from UserModule.

    To avoid collisions, applications should create their custom permissions with a minimum shift of 10. This still allows for 22 unique permissions, the range below 10 should be considered reserved for Across.

    The factory methods create(int) allow creation of a custom AclPermission using any bit position that is 10 or higher.

    Author:
    Arne Vandamme

    • Method Detail

      • create

        public static AclPermission create(int position)
        Create a new dynamic permission using the specified bit position. Because all bit positions below 10 are considered privileged, this method will throw an IllegalArgumentException if you attempt to create one. The same will happen if you attempt to go outside the integer range (max shift = 31).

        Specifying a position of 11 will result in a permission being created with a mask of 1 << 11.

        Parameters:
        position - bit position that should be used for this permission
        Returns:
        permission
